Rating: 4
This was very good, but I had to put my own twist on it as I do not like Tarragon. I added a clove of garlic to the potatoes, used less butter and some half and half and added minced green onion and parsley in place of the Tarragon. Then I doubled the wine, reduced it, added 2 tbsp of butter, then a grated clove of garlic, 2/3 cup of half and half, 2 more tbsp butter, salt and pepper, cooked this on very low heat, seared the scallops, deglazed the pan with a couple tbsp of water, added the deglazed pan juices, then green onion and parsley and a tbsp of parmesan cheese at the end. It was soooo yummy.

