Rating: 4
This is really delicious! I was attracted to this recipe because it didn't call for pasta as an accompaniment....a nice change of pace for scallops. I used Bay Scallops (about a handful per serving) instead of Sea Scallops, because that's what I had on hand. It's easy and delicious. I halved the recipe, because it was just my husband and I. I used dried tarragon, and only put 1 teaspoon into the sauce. I didn't add any to the potatoes, and it was just the right amount of seasoning. I served it with green beans. The longest part of preparing this dish is peeling and boiling the potatoes. Once they're boiled, the whole thing takes maybe 5 minutes, if you have all the ingredients ready! If you use new potatoes, you don't even have to peel them; just mash them with the skins. You can use your favorite type of potato for mashing, it doesn't have to be Yukon Gold. Wonderful recipe, and I will make this many more times!

